    "body": "Ok actually I located the error. In your second migrations file you use `deployer` in the place where an address should be for the `createOracle` function. You can't do this because `from` is expected to be an address while `deployer` is an object used for deploying. If you remove the argument from that function (or specify an address for `from` I presume) the error does not occur. Let me know if you are able to resolve this!",
